deck: The good guy created by a very bad man.
description:
Origin

In the year 1892, the days when the west was rough and tough, young Paul Nichols had seen his mother, father and two sisters shot down by ruthless cattle rustlers -- From that day onward he pledged himself against crime and at the age of 20 started his career as the Lone Avenger - A name feared by all crooks.

Creators

At one time (1947 – 1953) the most popular adventure comic book character in Australia, the Lone Avenger was created by Len Lawson, who would spend most of his life in prison after a series of heinous crimes that almost resulted in him getting the death penalty.

description:
Origin

Creation

Saint Don Quixote Homing (ドンキホーテ・ホーミング聖, Donkihōte Hōmingu Sei) is a supporting character in the One Piece series that was created by Eiichiro Oda. The series first began serialization in Shueisha's Weekly Shōnen Jump on August 4, 1997. He first appeared during the Dressrosa Arc that began in Volume 70.

His first appearance was in One Piece Volume ?? CH. 76o "The Same Bet".
